  m_text: '5. Procedural patterns (1)



    It is very common to employ procedural
    patterns in material design, both to improve realism and bypass the need for
    artist-made textures. We will see a couple of procedural materials, both noise-based
    and otherwise.


    We will start with a Mosaic material. However, first, we
    need to implement a hex-grid pattern. This would be created as a Subgraph: think
    about subgraphs as functions that we can invoke in Shaders. You can create one
    by right click > Create > Shader Graph > Sub Graph. For the scope of this lab,
    open Assets > Shaders > Hex Lattice.


    Once you''re done with that, open
    Assets > Shaders > Mosaic. Once completed, create a Material from it and try
    it on the plane on the right.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2100000, guid: e73a58f6e2794ae7b1b7e50b7fb811b0, type: 2}
