      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "3. Step-by-step: A textured shader\n\n\nWe will construct shaders step
    by step, starting with a simple pixel shader allowing us to apply a texture on
    objects. \n\nFirst off, to create shaders, go into Assets > Shaders, right click,
    and select Create > Shader Graph > URP > Lit Shader Graph. However, for this
    lab, we left instructions in pre-created ShaderGraph assets, so you will only
    work on those. Open Assets > Shaders > TexturedShader.\n\nOnce you're finished,
    create a material from the completed shader and drag it onto the sphere on the
    right.\n"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
