  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "1. Intro to Shading\n\n\nShaders are pieces of code that describe how
    a material interacts with light during rendering. \n\nBy defining how rays bounce
    off/go through a surface, or how they accumulate radiance from a surface hit,
    we can simulate a wide array of real-world behaviours. \n\nCombining these basics
    with (e.g.) noise functions, we can even achieve procedural materials, which
    can often be good enough to bypass the need for textures.\n\nIn many 3D graphics
    applications, shaders are defined in visual programming environment, with nodes
    identifying individual computations or pieces of data. We will take a look at
    Unity's ShaderGraph.\n"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2100000, guid: e73a58f6e2794ae7b1b7e50b7fb811b0, type: 2}
